WEBVTT

00:00.961 --> 00:02.587
<i>Previously on iZombie...</i>

00:02.796 --> 00:04.422
This is all we have.
One dose of the cure.

00:04.631 --> 00:05.799
<i>You turned me
into a zombie.</i>

00:06.007 --> 00:08.969
- Rather than watch you die.
- You let me check myself into
a mental hospital.

00:09.177 --> 00:10.845
You let me think I was crazy.

00:11.054 --> 00:12.889
- Whatever happens now,
I hope you can forgive me.
- Liv?

00:13.098 --> 00:14.432
I get it. You're not
talking to me.

00:14.641 --> 00:15.809
I just need some time.

00:16.017 --> 00:17.978
What do I need to
replicate the cure?

00:18.186 --> 00:20.814
Ah, yes. The tainted
Utopium from the night
of the boat massacre.

00:21.022 --> 00:21.648
Hey, Dad!

00:21.815 --> 00:24.609
<i>I showed up
to train a new client today,
and he was a zombie.</i>

00:24.818 --> 00:26.403
We've solved
the zombie problem.

00:26.611 --> 00:28.113
<i>We've located the instrument
of their destruction.</i>

00:28.321 --> 00:29.155
<i>There are zombies
living among us.</i>

00:29.364 --> 00:30.907
You want me to kill them?

00:31.116 --> 00:32.325
- Yes.
- You've got the wrong
man for the job.

00:32.534 --> 00:34.244
We do know of one zombie,
Liv Moore.

00:34.452 --> 00:36.413
I've got you over a barrel,
big guy.

00:36.621 --> 00:39.541
- Hey, roomie. How was work?
- You would not believe
the guy we hired.

00:39.749 --> 00:40.667
Ahh!

00:45.588 --> 00:47.966
<i>My father has been missing
for two days now.</i>

00:48.174 --> 00:50.760
<i>He's six-feet tall with brown
hair and brown eyes.</i>

00:53.513 --> 00:59.436
<i>If you've seen him, or heard
of anything at all, please
contact the Seattle Police.</i>

00:59.644 --> 01:01.896
<i>Please help us find our dad.</i>

01:02.105 --> 01:04.983
<i>We love him so much
and we just want
him to come home.</i>

01:05.191 --> 01:08.069
<i>Verna,
Verna, over here.
I have a question.</i>

01:14.743 --> 01:18.663
Friends, Romans, countrymen,

01:18.872 --> 01:23.168
lend me your beers!

01:23.376 --> 01:28.798
Four score and seven years
ago, and something,
something... Hail Caesar!

01:33.344 --> 01:34.679
Yo! What up, furry?

01:42.687 --> 01:45.065
Party foul!

02:21.226 --> 02:23.228
What happened to Caesar?

02:23.436 --> 02:26.022
Oh, he came, he saw,
he was stabbed several times
in quick succession

02:26.231 --> 02:28.566
with a sharp
cylindrical object.

02:28.775 --> 02:31.152
Likely an ice pick.
This is Chad Wolcoff.

02:31.361 --> 02:33.279
He was the pledge captain
for Zeta Beta Theta.

02:34.280 --> 02:35.240
Wait, don't move.

02:40.036 --> 02:42.038
These look like
the exact vials
from the boat party

02:42.247 --> 02:44.124
that contained
the tainted Utopium.

02:44.332 --> 02:46.417
Ravi, I'm pretty sure that
all Utopium comes
in vials like that.

02:46.626 --> 02:50.463
- Oh.
- And FYI, if you find the cure
for zombie-ism on this floor,

02:50.672 --> 02:52.757
I may opt
to keep eating brains.

02:52.966 --> 02:55.969
Room packed with people,
a guy gets stabbed
multiple times,

02:56.177 --> 02:57.804
and no one saw anything.

02:58.012 --> 03:00.098
- Seriously?
- I'm really gonna need
a hand with this,

03:00.306 --> 03:02.392
so let me know when things
get extrasensory.

03:04.936 --> 03:07.772
Well, I hope you like
Jager bombs
and homoerotic subtext.

03:16.948 --> 03:18.575
<i>- Can you meet me upstairs?</i>
- Yes.

03:22.954 --> 03:23.997
And so it begins...

03:29.043 --> 03:32.088
- You know what I fear
more than death?
- Love?

03:32.297 --> 03:35.049
Unrealized potential.

03:35.216 --> 03:39.804
I am overflowing with
potential, and I'm tapping
every last drop.

03:40.013 --> 03:43.808
How about you, Speedy?
You realizing your potential?

03:44.017 --> 03:47.145
I don't know if I'm
overflowing but, yeah.

03:47.353 --> 03:51.191
- All that stuff you said.
- That self-doubt?
That's Mr. Boss talking.

03:51.399 --> 03:54.944
We always said we wanted
more. More responsibility,
more money.

03:55.153 --> 03:57.197
I wanted to be alive to really
get to enjoy those things.

03:59.199 --> 04:02.160
He's not gonna take too
kindly to us moving in
on his Utopium trade.

04:02.368 --> 04:04.162
Hey, this is our time.

04:04.370 --> 04:06.748
Our product is better than
that glorified ecstasy he sells.

04:06.915 --> 04:07.832
Higher highs.

04:08.041 --> 04:08.958
Lower lows.

04:10.335 --> 04:11.461
Just saying.

04:11.669 --> 04:14.505
We're going to undercut
Mr. Boss' prices.

04:14.714 --> 04:18.509
Four dealers.
Four of the hottest clubs.
Opposite ends of the city.

04:18.718 --> 04:20.887
By the time Mr. Boss
knows what hit him,

04:21.095 --> 04:22.931
customers are gonna be
knocking down our door.

04:23.139 --> 04:26.768
And I've got
a big-ass roll of Benjamins.
Boys answering to me.

04:26.935 --> 04:28.519
Yes. Now...

04:28.728 --> 04:30.688
Our sales staff, did you find
what we were looking for?

04:30.897 --> 04:33.191
Upscale types, like you said.

04:33.399 --> 04:36.819
Rich kids whose daddies
cut them off.
Not the usual creepers.

04:37.028 --> 04:39.989
I don't want to know anything.
I'm just the little man
behind the curtain.

04:40.198 --> 04:44.494
No one needs to know I exist.
This is your show, okay?

04:44.702 --> 04:46.829
A year from now,
we'll be running this city.

04:47.705 --> 04:49.207
Your lips to God's ears.

04:49.415 --> 04:51.709
- Go. Go get 'em.
- Yeah.

04:57.048 --> 04:58.341
Sounds like a risky plan.

05:00.551 --> 05:02.637
Oh, and what?
You're the plan guy?

05:02.845 --> 05:06.557
Now, any progress finding
that guy who cut
the tainted Utopium?

05:06.766 --> 05:10.603
- Got a couple leads.
- Allow me to light
a fire under you.

05:10.812 --> 05:13.273
Do you know why
your brother was
institutionalized?

05:13.481 --> 05:18.111
Because he was crazy.
He heard voices.
He saw things.

05:18.319 --> 05:21.656
And the loony SOB
thought there were zombies
running around Seattle.

05:21.864 --> 05:23.157
That's just silly.

05:25.910 --> 05:27.829
Sometimes they just loiter.

05:28.037 --> 05:30.957
Chief, did I say
you could lick the bowl?

05:35.378 --> 05:38.089
It's, like, unthinkable that
someone murdered Chad.

05:38.298 --> 05:40.425
No, like, seriously,
I can't even think it.

05:40.633 --> 05:46.514
He was more than just
a frat brother. He was, like,
a brother-brother, bro.

05:46.723 --> 05:48.182
For real.

05:48.391 --> 05:50.560
Oh, hey, I think
we killed that.

05:52.353 --> 05:54.647
- What are you doing?
- Coaxing the flow to the hose.

06:01.612 --> 06:03.823
Did Chad have any enemies
that you know of?

06:04.032 --> 06:06.743
No way, man.
Chad was the freaking best.

06:06.951 --> 06:08.911
- Everybody loved him.
- Well, not everybody.

06:09.120 --> 06:10.621
I mean, someone
stabbed him to death.

06:11.706 --> 06:12.665
No disrespect, bro.

06:12.874 --> 06:14.250
No, no, bro. I feel you.

06:15.209 --> 06:17.003
Valid point.

06:17.211 --> 06:19.547
That person might be
a complete knob,
but they're out there.

06:19.756 --> 06:23.134
I don't know, like, who do you
guys know who totally sucks?

06:23.343 --> 06:25.178
Actually,
that's not important.

06:25.386 --> 06:26.971
Seems like
a solid jumping-off point,
bro.

06:27.180 --> 06:30.308
Guys, who you think sucks is
not helpful information.

06:30.516 --> 06:34.312
Hey! Hey! Did Chad ever
fight with anyone?

06:34.520 --> 06:37.648
Well, I mean, sometimes
dudes from other frats
would get pissed

06:37.857 --> 06:40.610
- because he crushed
so hard at pong.

06:40.818 --> 06:44.322
He was just a great guy.
He invented Stripper
Car Wash Sunday.

06:44.530 --> 06:47.325
Which sounds degrading,
but all the proceeds
went to charity.

06:47.533 --> 06:48.993
Dude, no, they didn't.

06:49.202 --> 06:51.204
Bro, that's why he didn't have
to pay the strippers.

06:51.412 --> 06:53.289
It all went to, like,
dyslexia research.

06:54.457 --> 06:55.500
The best was Chunk.

06:55.708 --> 06:57.210
Chunk! Ah!

06:57.418 --> 07:00.171
Chad buttered this fat guy's
floor while he was asleep.

07:00.380 --> 07:03.341
So dude gets up in
the morning, all naked, and
he's slipping around like

07:03.549 --> 07:05.760
a freaking walrus on ice.

07:05.968 --> 07:07.845
It's on YouTube.
You guys gotta see it.

07:08.054 --> 07:10.223
- Oh, yeah.
- See, that's just the kind of
guy Chad was, you know.

07:10.431 --> 07:14.060
You pass out drunk,
shave the eyebrows.
Maybe snap a ball-drag pic.

07:14.268 --> 07:16.813
Sounds like he might have
made some people upset.

07:17.021 --> 07:18.731
Maybe the victims
of these pranks?

07:18.940 --> 07:21.651
I guess like a little.
To everyone else it was
just super funny.

07:21.859 --> 07:23.528
Look, Chad wasn't just
pranks and stuff.

07:23.736 --> 07:25.530
Like, he was always there
for his brothers.

07:25.738 --> 07:28.032
When you're doing
your fourth funnel, and
you're not gonna puke,

07:28.241 --> 07:29.325
but you might still give up,

07:31.160 --> 07:36.707
he was the guy yelling,
"Chug! Chug!
Chug! Chug!"

07:38.709 --> 07:40.670
- Ready, bro?
- Let's do this, bro!

07:40.878 --> 07:42.213
- Chug! Chug!
- One, two, three.

07:45.049 --> 07:47.677
You ruined my life, man!
You ruined my life.

07:50.388 --> 07:51.347
Chug.

07:52.890 --> 07:54.016
I lost my champion, bro.

07:55.184 --> 07:56.394
I lost my champion.

07:59.730 --> 08:02.733
Hey, you. How did Chad
ruin your life?

08:06.404 --> 08:07.697
Damn!

08:14.120 --> 08:18.374
It was pledge week.
Chad made me streak.

08:18.583 --> 08:20.376
I didn't know I was streaking
by an elementary school

08:20.585 --> 08:22.253
till I heard the kids
start laughing.

08:22.462 --> 08:25.006
Not only was I arrested,

08:25.214 --> 08:27.216
I had to register
as a sex offender.

08:27.425 --> 08:28.926
So why stay with
the fraternity?

08:29.135 --> 08:33.264
Chad convinced me to.
My career prospects are
limited now.

08:33.473 --> 08:36.684
Chad assured me that
the Zeta Beta Thetas
take care of their own.

08:36.893 --> 08:39.437
As long as I'm a brother,
I have a future.

08:39.645 --> 08:41.647
Where were you at the time
of the murder?

08:41.856 --> 08:45.401
I was in the back room,
talking to some girl
in a sexy unicorn costume.

08:45.610 --> 08:47.487
We heard screams
and ran inside.

08:47.695 --> 08:48.571
I'll need the girl's name.

08:48.779 --> 08:50.865
She was just a random chick.

08:51.073 --> 08:53.201
Wait. I saw a photo on
the party's Instagram feed.

08:56.579 --> 08:57.914
Are these
all from the party?

08:58.122 --> 08:59.540
Yeah, look that is me
in the curtain.

08:59.749 --> 09:01.334
How am I supposed
to know that's you?

09:01.542 --> 09:03.503
A pterodactyl could be inside
there and no one would know.

09:03.711 --> 09:06.756
But it's me.
Look, I have the costume.

09:06.964 --> 09:09.634
All that tells me is
you have the costume that
an unidentified person

09:09.842 --> 09:11.802
- was wearing in this photo.
- But it's me.

09:12.011 --> 09:13.554
Okay, Brody will tell you.

09:17.058 --> 09:20.561
You know, these must've
been taken from
the top of the staircase.

09:20.770 --> 09:23.397
All right, there's Chad,
right?

09:23.606 --> 09:28.861
Still there, still there,
still there, gone.
Right? Let's go back.

09:29.070 --> 09:31.113
See this furry blue thing?

09:31.322 --> 09:33.658
You can see Chad as Furry Blue
is heading over,

09:33.866 --> 09:37.245
but look at this one of
Furry Blue walking away.
Chad's down.

09:37.453 --> 09:40.206
- Furry Blue is probably
who stabbed him.
- Okay...

09:40.414 --> 09:42.208
He doesn't remember
what I was wearing, but...

09:42.416 --> 09:44.293
Who wore
the Furry Blue costume?

09:45.878 --> 09:47.588
Yeah, I don't know
who the blue guy is,

09:47.797 --> 09:50.007
- but how huge are
Megan Reilly's cans?

09:50.216 --> 09:52.969
Oh, that's not Megan Reilly,
bro. Her cans are
more teardrop.

09:53.177 --> 09:54.095
Okay!

09:56.389 --> 09:57.431
Thank you for your time.

10:00.935 --> 10:05.398
- So, if I remember anything,
should I call you, or...
- You can call me.

10:05.606 --> 10:10.361
I'm the detective on the case.

10:10.570 --> 10:12.488
You're like that box of
chocolates from <i>Forrest Gump,</i>

10:12.697 --> 10:13.948
I never know
what I'm gonna get.

10:14.156 --> 10:16.117
You're getting chocolate, bro.

10:16.325 --> 10:19.078
I'll start calling
the local costume shops.

10:19.287 --> 10:22.415
See if I can
find the ones that stock that
blue furry costume.

10:22.623 --> 10:24.041
Find out who rented it.

10:26.794 --> 10:29.755
Chakrabarti! Where you at?

10:29.964 --> 10:32.592
I have been doing
some thinking,

10:32.800 --> 10:36.804
and I'm pretty sure
what this morgue needs
is a foosball table.

10:44.478 --> 10:47.940
I know you can't fully
control your actions
when you're on a brain,

10:48.149 --> 10:51.527
but I really need you to try
and rein in the bro.

10:51.736 --> 10:54.530
We would be in serious trouble
if someone came in
and saw how you arranged

10:54.739 --> 10:56.699
the medical skeletons.

10:56.907 --> 10:59.744
And this,
this is unacceptable.

11:01.537 --> 11:03.539
What if someone came in to
identify their loved one

11:03.748 --> 11:06.667
and the medical examiner
had "fart" written
on his forehead?

11:06.876 --> 11:09.378
It isn't funny.

11:09.587 --> 11:11.255
- It's pretty funny.
- It really isn't.

11:11.464 --> 11:13.966
- It kinda is.
- I can assure you
it isn't funny.

11:17.303 --> 11:19.221
It isn't funny.

11:19.430 --> 11:21.557
You're lucky you're receiving
a suspension and
not an expulsion.

11:21.766 --> 11:23.809
Okay.
But it's kind of funny.

11:24.018 --> 11:28.147
No. No, it's not.
It's not funny.

11:28.356 --> 11:33.402
- Were you contemplating your
actions or having a vision?
- If you had to guess...

11:33.611 --> 11:37.239
I take back every bad thing
I ever said about frat boys.

11:37.448 --> 11:39.283
These brains are fun as hell.

11:39.492 --> 11:42.453
I can't stop chillaxing.
Everything is hilarious.

11:42.662 --> 11:46.290
Dude, the guy who killed Chad
is a total dick,
and I demand...

11:46.499 --> 11:47.792
<i>Babineaux.</i>

11:48.000 --> 11:49.835
Wazzup? Just had a vis.

11:50.044 --> 11:53.172
Yeah, it was, like,
a discipline
hearing-type thing.

11:53.381 --> 11:56.425
This kid looked like he wanted
to murder Chad, bro.

11:56.634 --> 11:58.219
We've gotta find
this other student.

11:58.427 --> 11:59.887
Pronto.

12:00.096 --> 12:01.847
Brain fart.
Whole new level.

12:06.102 --> 12:08.312
So I finally found out
the blue bear is a character

12:08.521 --> 12:11.148
from a Swedish kids' show
named <i>Captain Wozzles.</i>

12:11.357 --> 12:13.359
He did look Nordic.

12:13.567 --> 12:16.404
I called every costume shop
here in Seattle.
So far, no one carries it.

12:16.612 --> 12:18.698
I'll move on to shops
in the surrounding area.

12:18.906 --> 12:22.201
But first, I spoke to the dean
of Pacific West University
about your vision.

12:22.410 --> 12:23.994
He wouldn't give me details
about the grievance filed

12:24.203 --> 12:26.205
against Chad
without a warrant,

12:26.414 --> 12:29.125
but said I was welcome to see
if the student was open to
discussing it.

12:29.333 --> 12:32.169
He's on his way in now.
And you'll never guess
what his name is.

12:32.378 --> 12:33.796
Chad Wolcoff.

12:34.004 --> 12:35.715
Like the murder victim.

12:35.923 --> 12:37.675
Can you tell us why
you filed a grievance
against Chad?

12:37.883 --> 12:39.969
Chad and I often got each
other's mail back at school.

12:40.177 --> 12:43.431
I got invited to speak
at a high school about
the dangers of drunk driving.

12:43.639 --> 12:45.307
Chad got my invitation
by mistake.

12:45.516 --> 12:50.187
He thought it would
be a hoot to get wasted
and go in my place.

12:50.396 --> 12:52.648
He basically gave a tutorial
on how to drink and drive

12:52.857 --> 12:56.444
to 200 high school seniors
before school security
dragged him off stage.

12:56.652 --> 12:58.821
Oh, hey,
I get why that's awful,

12:59.029 --> 13:01.574
but I think Chad was just
trying to be funny, you know.
I...

13:01.782 --> 13:05.077
Thirty people per day
are killed in
drunk driving accidents.

13:05.286 --> 13:07.496
Can you tell us
where you were last night,
around 10 p.m.?

13:09.498 --> 13:11.709
Uh...
I was in my room, studying.

13:11.917 --> 13:13.127
Anyone who can verify that?

13:15.755 --> 13:17.840
Doubtful. It's just...

13:18.048 --> 13:21.761
Look, I took the appropriate
actions with Chad, okay?

13:21.969 --> 13:24.013
I met with the dean.
I filed a complaint.

13:24.221 --> 13:27.850
Chad was a buffoon,
but I don't think
he deserved to die.

13:28.058 --> 13:33.022
All right. I'll contact you
with any further questions.
Don't leave town.

13:38.486 --> 13:42.531
Tightly wound,
but he didn't give me
a premeditated murder vibe.

13:42.740 --> 13:45.367
I'm guessing he lost
someone close to him in
a drunk-driving accident.

13:45.576 --> 13:47.703
Chad making light of that
could've made him snap.

13:47.912 --> 13:49.538
A sideways glance could've
made him snap.

13:49.747 --> 13:51.290
That dude has zero chill.

13:53.375 --> 13:55.085
Your blood pressure is
a bit higher than it's been.

13:55.294 --> 13:56.295
It might not be cure-related.

13:56.504 --> 13:57.588
Still feeling okay?

13:58.380 --> 14:00.007
Yeah.

14:00.216 --> 14:03.427
So, I know you're a student
of men's lifestyle magazines.

14:03.636 --> 14:06.388
Beard glitter.
Is this a trend
I should know about?

14:06.597 --> 14:07.807
It was an accident.

14:08.015 --> 14:10.059
Involving a My Little Pony?

14:10.267 --> 14:12.770
I had some makeup on before
that was surprisingly
difficult to wash off.

14:12.978 --> 14:15.064
Been there.
So, you know I'm
referring to your beard

14:15.272 --> 14:17.149
as Princess Sparkles
from now on though, right?

14:17.358 --> 14:18.818
Why would you be
referring to my beard?

14:19.026 --> 14:20.694
"You've got some crumbs
stuck in Princess Sparkles."

14:20.861 --> 14:23.572
Or, "Princess Sparkles
could use a trim."

14:26.617 --> 14:28.452
So, how's work going
on the cure?

14:28.661 --> 14:30.663
I can't make any progress
without tainted Utopium.

14:30.871 --> 14:33.499
I've run tests on regular
Utopium, but, to be honest,

14:33.707 --> 14:35.417
I know very little about
how the drug works.

14:35.626 --> 14:37.837
I mean, it's relatively new,
there aren't studies.

14:38.045 --> 14:40.381
Have you, you know,
ever tried any?

14:40.589 --> 14:42.174
You know hugs are
my drug of choice.

14:42.383 --> 14:44.009
I've been mulling it over,

14:44.218 --> 14:45.886
and I think it would be
beneficial for me to try some.

14:46.095 --> 14:47.471
You know, so I can better
understand its effects.

14:47.680 --> 14:49.223
Isn't that kind of like
smacking a bear

14:49.431 --> 14:51.684
- to better understand
being mauled to death?
- No.

14:51.892 --> 14:54.812
It's like smacking a bear to
better understand physical
exertion and adrenaline.

14:55.020 --> 14:57.189
Field research is
incredibly helpful.

14:57.398 --> 15:01.610
Experiencing how Utopium
works in the body could help
my research immeasurably.

15:01.819 --> 15:03.529
Would you come to
a club with me?

15:03.737 --> 15:05.197
I could use someone
to monitor me while
I'm on the drug.

15:05.406 --> 15:07.074
You know, make sure I'm safe,
help record data.

15:07.283 --> 15:09.034
Ravi, can't I just help you
move a couch or something?

15:09.243 --> 15:12.621
I'm really not up for the,
like, "Watch me do drugs"
favor.

15:12.830 --> 15:15.875
