33:46.401 --> 33:48.528
You get paid in brains.

33:48.695 --> 33:50.822
I'll have to grease a lot of
palms in order to get any
movement on this case.

33:51.030 --> 33:53.825
One in eight cops.
One in three judges.
Remember?

33:55.034 --> 33:56.536
I'll get you the cash.

33:56.744 --> 33:58.037
Do you have any idea
what you're starting here?

33:59.163 --> 34:00.164
I believe I do.

34:08.548 --> 34:10.967
Wakey-wakey, Speedy.

34:11.175 --> 34:13.845
- No. No. No!
- Mr. Boss sends his regards.

34:21.310 --> 34:25.773
And Alexander wept
when he realized there were
no more worlds to conquer.

34:25.982 --> 34:27.650
Did you weep, Angus?

34:27.859 --> 34:30.486
Let me guess, business
has been so bad

34:30.695 --> 34:32.196
you're reduced to making
your own deliveries.

34:32.405 --> 34:35.742
No. The only brains I brought
today are right up here.

34:35.950 --> 34:37.827
And wouldn't you love
a bite of those bad boys.

34:38.036 --> 34:40.580
No need. I've read <i>Oedipus.</i>

34:40.788 --> 34:45.835
Oedipus requires
a living mother, but, hey.

34:46.044 --> 34:48.129
How could you have seen
the warning signs?

34:48.337 --> 34:51.841
Don't all wives lock
themselves alone in their room
for weeks at a time,

34:52.050 --> 34:54.052
claiming they want to die?

34:54.260 --> 34:56.846
And why would it even occur to
you to lock up your Beretta?

34:57.055 --> 34:59.390
You're a whiny bitch.

34:59.599 --> 35:01.476
So obvious that you
didn't get that from me.

35:01.684 --> 35:05.980
What was it Madonna said?
"Papa, don't preach."

35:06.189 --> 35:10.193
And business is booming,
thank you for asking.
My client list keeps growing,

35:10.401 --> 35:13.529
but don't worry.
You never forget
your first customer.

35:13.738 --> 35:16.616
Son turns father
into a member
of the undead.

35:16.824 --> 35:22.121
Gee. Why did Oedipus
even cross my mind?
What is it you want?

35:22.330 --> 35:26.876
What does anyone ever want
from you, Angus? Money.

35:27.085 --> 35:29.212
Lots of it.

35:29.420 --> 35:32.381
On top of the 25k
a month for brains? Whoo!

35:32.590 --> 35:34.926
You should learn to
live within your means.

35:35.134 --> 35:39.806
If you don't mind,
what shortcut are you
taking this time, huh?

35:40.014 --> 35:45.061
It's always the same for you,
isn't it? Always looking for
the easy way out.

35:45.269 --> 35:49.023
Least amount of
talent required.

35:50.608 --> 35:53.319
Least amount of effort.

35:53.528 --> 35:57.115
What does the PowerPoint look
like for your inspirational
climb up the ladder?

35:57.323 --> 36:01.285
Step one. Have your father
who built the company
institutionalized.

36:01.494 --> 36:03.955
Step two. Move
into his office.

36:04.163 --> 36:06.916
Your Horatio Alger story
was a phone call.

36:11.754 --> 36:17.343
The strings I pulled to
get my party boy son
into Wharton.

36:19.595 --> 36:21.222
You couldn't make it
one semester.

36:23.349 --> 36:27.520
"Dad. Dad, Dad,
Dad, Dad, Dad...

36:27.728 --> 36:31.315
"This widget's gonna
revolutionize the way
we listen to music,

36:31.524 --> 36:33.943
"rent apartments, hook up.

36:34.152 --> 36:37.446
"I just need some
startup capital."

36:37.655 --> 36:40.449
I always knew
the request was coming,
because you'd manage

36:40.658 --> 36:46.038
to hide your hate for me
for a few weeks
leading up to the pitch.

36:46.247 --> 36:51.002
And I would just give in.
I guess that's
how this story ends.

36:51.210 --> 36:53.546
No.

36:53.754 --> 36:58.593
This story ends with me taking
this chair, this desk, this
office, your entire company.

36:58.801 --> 37:01.512
The only thing that means
anything to you.

37:01.721 --> 37:06.309
I'll watch you walk out of
here with a cardboard box
full of paperclips and K-Cups.

37:06.517 --> 37:09.270
It's the dream that gets me
out of bed each day.

37:09.478 --> 37:11.647
And after I watch
that play out,

37:11.856 --> 37:14.775
I'm gonna stick you
in the same hellhole
where you stuck Grandpa.

37:16.194 --> 37:19.071
- He babied you.
- He loved me.

37:19.280 --> 37:20.823
You just don't know
the difference.

37:28.956 --> 37:30.791
Make it out for
half a million.

37:31.500 --> 37:32.835
Look at me.

37:33.044 --> 37:35.671
Chip off the old block.

37:35.880 --> 37:37.882
Katy Perry.
Kate Upton.
Kate Middleton.

37:38.090 --> 37:41.427
I mean, all three
doable and datable.
This game is impossible.

37:43.471 --> 37:45.473
By the time I got the Captain
Wozzles costume from the shop,

37:45.681 --> 37:47.266
it had already been laundered.

37:47.475 --> 37:48.851
I was hoping Forensics could
still get something off of it.

37:49.060 --> 37:50.186
I'm kind of glad
they couldn't,

37:50.394 --> 37:52.521
after what our furry
friends told us.

37:54.315 --> 37:57.860
Hmm... Do
Dylan McDermott.
Date Bob Dylan.

37:58.069 --> 37:59.487
Delete Dermot Mulroney.

37:59.695 --> 38:01.405
Really? Did you not see
his turn on <i>New Girl?</i>

38:01.614 --> 38:03.449
- I found him delightful.
- Oh, I thought
Dylan McDermott was

38:03.658 --> 38:05.451
from <i>My Best Friend's Wedding.</i>

38:05.618 --> 38:08.246
- Mmm-mmm, that's
Dermot Mulroney.
- I deleted the wrong Dermot!

38:09.455 --> 38:11.624
Wait a minute.

38:11.832 --> 38:14.877
- What if...
- What if the wrong guy
got killed?

38:15.086 --> 38:18.464
I couldn't find a connection
to you and the murder victim

38:18.673 --> 38:20.132
because there wasn't one.

38:20.341 --> 38:22.593
But I've got some bad news
for you, son.

38:22.802 --> 38:24.804
This Chad Wolcoff,
the one you killed,

38:25.012 --> 38:27.640
he's not who ran over
your father in
a drunk-driving accident.

38:27.848 --> 38:28.808
No, that would be

38:30.059 --> 38:32.019
this Chad Wolcoff,

38:32.228 --> 38:33.896
from your hometown of Spokane.

38:34.105 --> 38:35.690
You murdered an innocent man.

38:35.898 --> 38:39.193
Chad Wolcoff of Spokane,
the one you believed
you were killing,

38:39.402 --> 38:41.404
has spent the past five years
speaking at high schools

38:41.612 --> 38:43.406
about the dangers
of drunk driving.

38:43.614 --> 38:45.491
He was trying to make amends
for what he did
to your family.

38:58.087 --> 39:03.968
My dad was working
up on Highway 2,
putting in a guardrail.

39:04.176 --> 39:10.057
This drunk 15-year-old kid
doing 95 skids right into him.

39:12.560 --> 39:16.480
All I knew about the guy
who killed Dad was he was
a few years older than me

39:19.108 --> 39:21.861
and his name was Chad Wolcoff.

39:22.069 --> 39:25.448
Every once in a while,
I would google
this Chad Wolcoff.

39:25.656 --> 39:28.701
Until I finally
got a hit last year.
He was the right age.

39:29.910 --> 39:30.953
I had to see him,

39:32.580 --> 39:35.624
the guy who destroyed
my family.

39:35.833 --> 39:38.586
And when I did,
he was just this idiot drunk,

39:38.794 --> 39:40.421
and he didn't care
that he killed my dad.

39:43.132 --> 39:45.217
He didn't have
a care in the world.

39:45.426 --> 39:51.891
And now you're saying that
this wasn't him?

39:52.099 --> 39:55.269
That this is just some guy?
And he didn't do anything?

39:56.437 --> 39:57.438
He didn't do anything?

39:59.190 --> 40:00.232
He didn't do anything.

40:01.150 --> 40:03.486
Oh, no.

40:07.114 --> 40:10.326
You have the right
to remain silent.

40:10.534 --> 40:14.246
Anything you say can
and will be used against
you in a court of law.

40:14.455 --> 40:17.291
<i>Our lives are
a collection of choices.</i>

40:17.500 --> 40:19.960
<i>Sonny chose to
avenge his father.</i>

40:20.169 --> 40:23.506
<i>I chose to not tell my
fiance I'm a zombie.</i>

40:23.714 --> 40:25.841
<i>We make our own beds.</i>

40:26.050 --> 40:28.427
<i>Seems beneath our dignity
to whine when we're
forced to sleep in them.</i>

40:30.554 --> 40:32.348
<i>But Major held me...
Held me and told me</i>

40:32.556 --> 40:35.559
<i>he wouldn't let anything
happen to me.</i>

40:35.768 --> 40:38.979
<i>Maybe,
just this once,
there's a do-over.</i>

40:40.564 --> 40:42.650
- Hey.
- Major left a message.

40:42.858 --> 40:45.277
He wanted me to come
pick up the replacement
cell phone he bought for me.

40:45.486 --> 40:47.738
The phone. Yeah.
Of course. Here.

40:50.616 --> 40:52.743
Oh. I thought he'd be home.

40:52.952 --> 40:54.537
Oh, no, he is.
He is. He's...

40:54.745 --> 40:57.915
It's fine.
I just want to go say "Hi."

40:58.124 --> 41:00.709
We're back on speaking terms.
Baby steps, I know.

41:08.634 --> 41:09.677
Major? It's me.

41:11.429 --> 41:12.680
I left the phone with Ravi.

41:13.764 --> 41:15.182
I just wanted to say "Hi."

41:16.892 --> 41:18.102
Kinda busy.
